I"ð<p>The international New Interfaces for Musical Expression conference takes place at Goldsmiths University this year. <a href="http://www.nime2014.org/">NIME</a> has become one of the key academic conferences in computer music and music technology research. The conference promises to be very interesting this year, organised by a fantastic team of people at the <a href="http://www.gold.ac.uk/computing/">Department of Computing</a>. The Music Informatics and Performance Technologies Lab will have a strong presence at NIME, presenting a range of research and performances:</p>

<p>Chris Kiefer presents his paper on <a href="http://nime2014.sched.org/event/9375b0d246b367b7c494bed00c7c94a4#.U4xaHF40v9o">Musical Instrument Mapping Design with Echo State Networks</a></p>

<p>Thor Magnusson presents his paper called <a href="http://nime2014.sched.org/event/77f7feac0abd54d7a40829f4dedae268#.U4xaZF40v9o">Improvising with the Threnoscope: Integrating Code, Hardware, GUI, Network, and Graphic Scores</a> and participates in an <a href="http://notation.afim-asso.org/doku.php/evenements/2014-06-30-nimew">Interactive Music Notation and Representation Workshop</a> with a presentation on Algorithmic Notation.</p>

<p>Thor Magnusson and Adriana Sa perform a piece called <a href="http://nime2014.sched.org/event/cab573a5aa9e9ff144baeb904d47e5b8#.U4xanl40v9o">Fermata</a>.</p>

<p>Sally Jane Norman is co-organising a panel on <a href="http://nime2014.sched.org/event/b29e012f6aa292b32d70ca5f24967602#.U4xcqF40v9o">Gender, Education, Creativity in Digital Music and Sound Art</a>.</p>

<p>Chad McKinney has a poster on <a href="http://nime2014.sched.org/event/8f579cc3102bf42b639f0ea37dc08c6c#.U4xZ1l40v9o">Quick Live Coding Collaboration In The Web Browser</a></p>

<p>Nick Collins presents <a href="http://nime2014.sched.org/speaker/nickcollinsandadindavantklooster#.U4xbBl40v9o">various work</a></p>

<p>Matt Yee-King with Alex McLean perform <a href="http://nime2014.sched.org/artist/matthewyeeking#.U4xbFl40v9o">Canute</a>.</p>
